           Ê 
         
          
             
            Sol Ideas Technology Development is a consulting firm that provides 
            expertise in the application of optics and semiconductor materials 
            used for photovoltaics (PV), renewable energy, and optoelectronics. 
            As a Materials Scientist and specialist in solar concentrators, Greg 
            P. Smestad, Ph.D. offers consulting for R&D in solar cells, peer review, 
            merit review, scientific evaluation, scientific due diligence and 
            technical training on these topics. Our clients range from government 
            agencies to companies and individuals. 
             
            The word "Sol" comes from the Spanish word for Sun, and Sol Ideas 
            Technology Development helps those with "Ideas" that can lead to a 
            cleaner environment. 
             
             
             
               
                  Our expertise stems from: 
                   
                     editorial work for  Solar 
                      Energy Materials and Solar Cells  
                     solar cell and photovoltaic technology  consulting 
                      services  
                     a solar cell book -  Optoelectronics 
                      of Solar Cells  
                      20 years in Solar Energy  
                     Due diligence / peer review (e.g.,  U.S. 
                      Department of Energy ) 
                     a long standing  commitment 
                      to education  
                     development of an  educational 
                      solar cell kit  
                   
